<concept
	id="programmatic-region-creation">
	<title>Programmatic Region Creation</title>
	<shortdesc>You create regions programmatically with the <codeph>regionFactory</codeph> class. </shortdesc>
	<conbody>
		<note>
			<p>Before creating a region, specify region attributes. See <xref
				href="region-attributes.xml#region-attributes"
				type="concept"
				format="dita"
				scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Region Attributes?></xref>.
			</p>
		</note>
		<p>Create your regions using the <codeph>regionFactory</codeph> class.</p>
		<p>
			<b>C++ RegionFactory Example</b></p>
			<codeblock>
RegionFactoryPtr regionFactory =
    cachePtr-&gt;createRegionFactory(CACHING_PROXY);
RegionPtr regPtr0 = regionFactory-&gt;setLruEntriesLimit(20000)
        -&gt;create("exampleRegion0");
	</codeblock>
		<note>For more information on how to create a region, see <xref
				href="../cpp-caching-api/cpp-caching-api.xml#concept_CEC658A999414AC3A494578C214BF64E"
				type="concept" format="dita" scope="local"
				><?xm-replace_text vFabric GemFire Native Client C++ API?></xref>, <xref
				href="../dotnet-caching-api/dotnet-caching-api.xml#concept_FC6776DCE6ED48B887A6137761104AA4"
				type="concept" format="dita" scope="local"
				><?xm-replace_text vFabric GemFire Native Client C# .NET API?></xref>, and the
			native client API reference. </note>
	</conbody>
</concept>
